#Dengue Data
data.labels <- fread("dengue_labels_train.csv")
data.labels.sj <- data.labels[city=="sj"]
data.labels.iq <- data.labels[city=="iq"]
#Additional Variables
data.features <- fread("dengue_features_train.csv")
data.features.sj <- data.features[city=="sj"]
data.features.iq <- data.features[city=="iq"]
#Merge
data.sj <- merge(data.labels.sj, data.features.sj, by.x = c("year","weekofyear","city"), 
              by.y = c("year","weekofyear","city"), all.x = TRUE, all.y = TRUE)
data.iq <- merge(data.labels.iq, data.features.iq, by.x = c("year","weekofyear","city"), 
              by.y = c("year","weekofyear","city"), all.x = TRUE, all.y = TRUE)

#SJ Correlated Variables

#Define regressors SJ
external.reg.sj <- cbind(data.sj[,"year"],data.sj[,"weekofyear"],data.sj[,"reanalysis_air_temp_k"],data.sj[,"reanalysis_avg_temp_k"],
                 data.sj[,"reanalysis_dew_point_temp_k"],data.sj[,"reanalysis_max_air_temp_k"],data.sj[,"reanalysis_min_air_temp_k"],
                 data.sj[,"reanalysis_precip_amt_kg_per_m2"],data.sj[,"reanalysis_relative_humidity_percent"],
                 data.sj[,"reanalysis_specific_humidity_g_per_kg"],data.sj[,"station_avg_temp_c"],data.sj[,"station_max_temp_c"],
                 data.sj[,"station_min_temp_c"])
external.reg.sj.train <- external.reg.sj[1:749]
external.reg.sj.test <- external.reg.sj[750:936]

#Define regressors IQ
external.reg.iq <- cbind(data.iq[,"year"],data.iq[,"reanalysis_dew_point_temp_k"],data.iq[,"reanalysis_min_air_temp_k"],
                 data.iq[,"reanalysis_specific_humidity_g_per_kg"],data.iq[,"station_min_temp_c"])
external.reg.iq.train <- external.reg.iq[1:416]
external.reg.iq.test <- external.reg.iq[417:520]

#Set up SJ Time series
data.sj.ts <- ts(data.sj$total_cases, start = c(1990, 18), frequency = 52)
#Set up IQ Time Series
data.iq.ts <- ts(data.iq$total_cases, start = c(2000, 26), frequency = 52)

#SJ Data (80:20 split)
data.sj.end <- length(data.sj.ts)
data.sj.train.cutoff <- round(.8*data.sj.end, 0)
data.sj.train <- data.sj.ts[1:data.sj.train.cutoff]
data.sj.test <- data.sj.ts[(data.sj.train.cutoff+1):data.sj.end]
data.sj.train.ts <- ts(data.sj.train, start = c(1990, 18), frequency = 52)
data.sj.test.ts <- ts(data.sj.test, start = c(2004, 39), frequency = 52)
#IQ Data (80:20 split)
data.iq.end <- length(data.iq.ts)
data.iq.train.cutoff <- round(.8*data.iq.end, 0)
data.iq.train <- data.iq.ts[1:data.iq.train.cutoff]
data.iq.test <- data.iq.ts[(data.iq.train.cutoff+1):data.iq.end]
data.iq.train.ts <- ts(data.iq.train, start = c(2000, 26), frequency = 52)
data.iq.test.ts <- ts(data.iq.test, start = c(2008, 27), frequency = 52)

#Dengue Data
data.submission <- fread("submission_format.csv")
data.submission.sj <- data.submission[city=="sj"]
data.submission.iq <- data.submission[city=="iq"]
#Additional Variables
data.submission.features <- fread("dengue_features_test.csv")
data.submission.features.sj <- data.submission.features[city=="sj"]
data.submission.features.iq <- data.submission.features[city=="iq"]
#Merge
data.submission.merge.sj <- merge(data.submission.sj, data.submission.features.sj, by.x = c("year","weekofyear","city"), 
                   by.y = c("year","weekofyear","city"), all.x = TRUE, all.y = TRUE)
data.submission.merge.iq <- merge(data.submission.iq, data.submission.features.iq, by.x = c("year","weekofyear","city"), 
                   by.y = c("year","weekofyear","city"), all.x = TRUE, all.y = TRUE)

#External Regressors SJ
submission.regressors.sj <- cbind(data.submission.merge.sj[,"year"],data.submission.merge.sj[,"weekofyear"],
                      data.submission.merge.sj[,"reanalysis_air_temp_k"], data.submission.merge.sj[,"reanalysis_avg_temp_k"],
                    data.submission.merge.sj[,"reanalysis_dew_point_temp_k"],data.submission.merge.sj[,"reanalysis_max_air_temp_k"],
                    data.submission.merge.sj[,"reanalysis_min_air_temp_k"],data.submission.merge.sj[,"reanalysis_precip_amt_kg_per_m2"],
                    data.submission.merge.sj[,"reanalysis_relative_humidity_percent"],data.submission.merge.sj[,"reanalysis_specific_humidity_g_per_kg"],
                    data.submission.merge.sj[,"station_avg_temp_c"],data.submission.merge.sj[,"station_max_temp_c"],data.submission.merge.sj[,"station_min_temp_c"])
submission.regressors.sj.test <- submission.regressors.sj

#External Regressors IQ
submission.regressors.iq <- cbind(data.submission.merge.iq[,"year"],data.submission.merge.iq[,"reanalysis_dew_point_temp_k"],
                                  data.submission.merge.iq[,"reanalysis_min_air_temp_k"],
                                  data.submission.merge.iq[,"reanalysis_specific_humidity_g_per_kg"],
                                  data.submission.merge.iq[,"station_min_temp_c"])
submission.regressors.iq.test <- submission.regressors.iq

#Model 1 ARIMA with external regressors for SJ
m1.sj <-stlf(data.sj.ts,method="arima",h=260,
                     xreg=as.matrix(external.reg.sj),
                     newxreg=as.matrix(submission.regressors.sj))
## Warning in forecast.forecast_ARIMA(fit, h = h, level = level, xreg = newxreg): Upper prediction
## intervals are not finite.
#Set negative forecasts to 0, carry forward on NAs
num.m1.sj <- as.numeric(m1.sj$mean)
num.m1.sj <- na.locf(num.m1.sj)
num.m1.sj[num.m1.sj<0] = 0
ts.num.m1.sj <- ts(num.m1.sj, start = c(2008, 18), frequency = 52)
#Plot and Train Accuracy
autoplot(m1.sj)

acc.m1.sj <- accuracy(m1.sj)
acc.m1.sj
##                      ME     RMSE      MAE  MPE MAPE      MASE        ACF1
## Training set 0.01532087 13.51447 7.912431 -Inf  Inf 0.2170009 0.005968251
# NNAR with regressors SJ Model
set.seed(125893)
#Deal with NAs in Xreg Test
submission.reg.sj.test.na <- data.table(submission.regressors.sj.test)
submission.reg.sj.test.na <- na.locf(submission.reg.sj.test.na)
#Model
m2.sj <- nnetar(data.sj.ts, xreg = as.matrix(external.reg.sj))
## Warning in nnetar(data.sj.ts, xreg = as.matrix(external.reg.sj)): Missing values in xreg, omitting
## rows
for.submission.m2.sj <- forecast(m2.sj,260, xreg = as.matrix(submission.reg.sj.test.na))

#Set negative forecasts to 0, carry forward on NAs
num.m2.sj <- as.numeric(for.submission.m2.sj$mean)
num.m2.sj <- na.locf(num.m2.sj)
num.m2.sj[num.m2.sj<0] = 0
ts.num.m2.sj <- ts(num.m2.sj, start = c(2008, 18), frequency = 52)
#Plot and Train Accuracy
plot(for.submission.m2.sj) + autolayer(ts.num.m2.sj)

## NULL
acc.m2.sj <- accuracy(for.submission.m2.sj)
acc.m2.sj
##                       ME     RMSE      MAE  MPE MAPE       MASE        ACF1
